  "prompt": "Is TCP IP dead?",
  "response": "No, TCP/IP is not dead. TCP/IP (Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol) remains the foundational technology for the vast majority of internet and network communications. Despite the emergence of newer protocols and networking technologies, TCP/IP continues to be widely used due to its robustness, scalability, and compatibility with a wide range of devices and applications. While there may be ongoing developments and enhancements to networking technologies, TCP/IP is still very much alive and central to the functioning of the internet.",
